There are 1011 apartments, away more than condos (614) and cooperatives(387) in long island, rendering 182615 unites in the house market.

Hempstead, Long Beach, Babylon, and Islip tend to be more crowded with multi-family housings. In general, when it gets closer to New York City, there are more multi-family housings: Nassau County has more. These could be apartments, condos, and cooperatives.


Methodology:

This web app aims to help users navigating through the Long Island multi-family housing market. The data is prepared by Suffolk County Planning at December 11, 2019.

The map is based on Python Leaflet library. Clusters are created by location, using the "MarkerCluster" function.

Each pin contains information about address and housing types, including apartment (APT), condo (COND), and cooperative (COOP).
